    "details": {
      "cr": 8,
      "type": {
        "value": "undead"
      },
      "alignment": "neutral evil",
      "biography": {
        "value": "\n                        Once a brilliant mortal wizard obsessed with cheating death, this individual delved too deep into necromantic arts. Through a forbidden ritual and a pact with dark entities, they achieved a form of undeath, becoming a lich-like entity. Their pursuit of ultimate arcane mastery continues, with the creation of an undead army and the acquisition of powerful artifacts being their primary goals. They are particularly interested in souls and the secrets they hold.\n                        <hr>\n                        <p><strong>Behavior:</strong> The lich-like wizard is a cold, calculating entity driven by an insatiable thirst for forbidden knowledge and power. It views living beings as mere tools or obstacles, to be manipulated, animated as undead servants, or destroyed if they stand in its way. It prefers to engage from a distance, using its potent spells to overwhelm and disintegrate foes, only resorting to direct confrontation when necessary or when its pride is sufficiently wounded.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Appearance:</strong> Gaunt and desiccated, this undead being is draped in tattered, yet once-fine, dark robes. Its eyes burn with an unnatural, malevolent green light within sunken sockets, and its skeletal fingers are adorned with ancient, dark rings. A faint aura of decay and cold emanates from its withered form.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Twist:</strong> The wizard is not truly dead, but bound to a powerful artifact (the Amulet of the Void) that sustains its undeath and amplifies its magical abilities. If the amulet is destroyed, the wizard will rapidly decay and cease to exist, unless it can transfer its consciousness to a new vessel.</p>\n                        <p><strong>Habitat:</strong> Unknown</p>\n                        <p><strong>Treasure:</strong> The lich-like wizard carries a Spellbook, an Amulet of the Void (which is its phylactery), and wears Robes of the Archmagi. It may also have a collection of rare spell components and arcane artifacts.</p>\n                    "
      },
